{"claim_id": 1, "claim": "Donald Trump delivered the largest tax cuts in American history.", "evidence": [{"question": "Did the tax cuts under Donald Trump's presidency constitute the largest tax cuts in American history?", "answer": "The Committee for a Responsible Budget crunched the numbers and said President Trump's tax cuts would be the eighth-largest in US history, measured as a percentage of GDP (to do so, they used a study from the US Treasury that looked at the impact of tax reform bills passed in the US between 1940 and 2012).", "url": "https://www.bbc.com/news/world-43790895"}, {"question": "Did the 2017 tax bill deliver the largest tax cuts in American history?", "answer": "Meanwhile, President Trump's tax cut would be the 4th largest in inflation-adjusted dollars since 1940.", "url": "https://www.crfb.org/blogs/president-trumps-tax-cut-largest-history-yet"}, {"question": "Did Donald Trump's tax cut proposal deliver the largest tax cuts in American history?", "answer": "President Trump has often stated that his proposed tax cut will be the largest in history. We previously found his $5.5 trillion framework in April would have been among the largest but not the largest.", "url": "https://www.crfb.org/blogs/president-trumps-tax-cut-largest-history-yet"}, {"question": "How much would a tax cut of the size that would exceed the record set in 1981 cost over a ten-year period?", "answer": "If President Trump wanted to pass a tax cut that exceeds the record 2.9 percent of the economy in 1981, it would cost roughly $6.8 trillion over ten years.", "url": "https://www.crfb.org/blogs/president-trumps-tax-cut-largest-history-yet"}, {"question": "Did the 2017 tax bill deliver the largest tax cuts in American history?", "answer": "In inflation-adjusted dollars, the recent tax bill is the fourth-largest since 1940. And as a percentage of GDP, it ranks seventh.", "url": "https://www.freep.com/story/news/politics/elections/2020/08/26/rnc-2020-fact-check/3441820001/"}, {"