n account. From the OAGF records, total remittances to the Federation account (less Joint Venture cash calls and cost of collection to DPR) from mineral revenue for 2017 amounted to N2.914 Trillion while non-mineral revenue (less 4% and 7% collection fees paid to both FIRS and NCS respectively) amounted to N1.767 Trillion.", "url": "https://web.archive.org/web/20200929223259/https://www.neiti.gov.ng/index.php/revenue-allocation"}, {"question": "What percentage of revenue is allocated to states according to the 1999 Constitution of the Federal Republic of Nigeria?", "answer": "Federation revenue is therefore owned by the three federating units. Section 162 of the 1999 Constitution of the Federal Republic of Nigeria defines “revenue” as any income or returns accruing to or derived by the Government of the Federation from any source including:", "url": "https://web.archive.org/web/20200929223259/https://www.neiti.gov.ng/index.php/revenue-allocation"}, {"question": "Does the 13% derivation fund deducted from net mineral revenue affect the percentage of revenue that goes to states in Nigeria?", "answer": "The 13% derivation fund is deducted from net mineral revenue first before the rest is shared among all states.", "url": "https://web.archive.org/web/20200929223259/https://www.neiti.gov.ng/index.php/revenue-allocation"}, {"question": "According to the NEITI FASD Report (2007-2011), what percentage of Nigeria's revenue is allocated to states?", "answer": "For more details on the process of collection of federation revenue, the vertical and horizontal sharing models, see NEITI FASD Report (2007-2011).", "url": "https://web.archive.org/web/20200929223259/https://www.neiti.gov.ng/index.php/revenue-allocation"}, {"question": "What percentage of Nigeria's revenue is allocated to states according to the current Revenue Allocation Formula?", "answer": "The current Revenue Allocation Formula and distribution of Federation Account Revenue among the three tiers of Government are:", "url": "https://web.archive.org/web/20200929223259/https://www.neiti.gov.ng/index.php/revenue-allocation"}, {"question": "What percentage of Nigeria's revenue is allocated to states according to the vertical formula determined by RMAFC and approved by the National Assembly?", "answer": "Revenue is shared in accordance with the vertical formula, as determined by RMAFC and approved by the National Assembly.", "url": "https://web.archive.org/web/20200929223259/https://www.neiti.gov.ng/index.php/revenue-allocation"}, {"question": "What percentage of the revenue collected by the Federal Government in Nigeria is allocated to the states?", "answer": "All revenues accruing to the Federal Government (after deductions) end up in the Federation account and forms part of revenue that is utilized in funding the national budget.", "url": "https://web.archive.org/web/20200929223259/https://www.neiti.gov.ng/index.php/revenue-allocation"}], "pred_label": "Refuted", "llm_output": "<|start_header_id|>assistant<|end_header_id|>

