{"claim_id": 8, "claim": "Joe Biden voted for the Irag War and supported war in Serbia, Syria and Libya.", "evidence": [{"question": "What was the timing of Joe Biden's vote for the Iraq War resolution in relation to his hearing from Tenet in a classified session?", "answer": "Biden voted for the Iraq war resolution on October 11, 2002, three weeks after hearing from Tenet in the classified session.", "url": "https://theintercept.com/2020/01/07/joe-biden-iraq-war-history/"}, {"question": "Did Joe Biden support the use of military force in response to the 9/11 terrorist attacks?", "answer": "Biden did not oppose the US invasion of Afghanistan. As a US senator from Delaware, he joined his Senate colleagues in a unanimous vote in support of the 2001 resolution that authorized the use of military force against “nations, organizations, or persons” President George W. Bush determined were behind the terrorist attacks of September 11, 2001.", "url": "https://www.cnn.com/2019/12/31/politics/fact-check-biden-buttigieg-iraq-afghanistan/index.html"}, {"question": "What resolution did Joe Biden vote for regarding the Iraq War?", "answer": "It is noteworthy, then, that Biden voted against an amendment sponsored by then-Sen. Carl Levin (D-Michigan) that would have authorized U.S. military action against Iraq if the UN Security Council approved the use of force and instead voted for the resolution that essentially authorized President George W. Bush to invade Iraq at the time and circumstances of his own choosing.", "url": "https://truthout.org/articles/bidens-support-of-iraq-war-shows-how-he-would-run-the-white-house/"}, {"question": "Did Joe Biden's stance on the Iraq War change over time?", "answer": "Twice in the last five weeks, Joe Biden has claimed that despite voting to authorize military force against Iraq in 2002, he opposed the Iraq war from “the moment” it began.", "url": "https://www.factcheck.org/2019/09/bidens-record-on-iraq-war/"}, {"question": "Did Joe Biden support the Iraq War resolution before it was revised to include stronger conditions?", "answer": "Some context is needed to understand Clinton’s position in this debate. In September 2002, one month before Congress passed the resolution, Joseph Biden and Richard Lugar—the Senate Foreign Relations Committee’s chairman and ranking Republican member, respectively—drafted an alternative bill, authorizing the use of force only after Bush made a stronger case that Saddam possessed WMDs.", "url": "https://slate.com/news-and-politics/2016/02/hillary-clinton-told-the-truth-about-her-iraq-war-vote.html"}, {"question": "Did Joe Biden express regret for his vote to authorize the use of military force in Iraq?", "answer": "During the second Democratic primary debate on July 31, Biden said his “bad judgment” in voting to authorize President George W. Bush to use military force against Iraq in 2002 was “trusting the president saying he was only doing this to get inspectors in and get the U.N. to agree to put inspectors in.”", "url": "https://www.factcheck.org/2019/09/bidens-record-on-iraq-war/"}, {"question": "Did Joe Biden's decision to vote for the Iraq War in 2002 rely on his trust in President George W. Bush?", "answer": "Joe Biden says that when deciding whether to vote in favor of invading Iraq in 2002, he took President George W. Bush at his word and was led astray.", "url": "https://www.vox.com/policy-and-politics/2019/10/15/20849072/joe-biden-iraq-history-democrats-election-2020"}, {"question": "Did Joe Biden vote for a U.S. policy of regime change in Iraq, as well as support war in other countries like Serbia and Syria?", "answer": "And Sanders had previously voiced his support for a U.S. policy to oust Hussein. In the years leading up to the war, Sanders voted for a U.S. policy of regime change, for example in 1996 in response to Hussein's having sent troops into Kurdish territory, and in October 1998 he backed the Iraq Liberation Act, which made regime change official U.S. policy.", "url": "https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/2020-election/sanders-opposition-iraq-war-was-more-complicated-he-presents-n1137541"}, {"question": "What was Joe Biden's stance on the Iraq War, as reflected in his Senate vote in October 2002?", "answer": "Following his comments about Afghanistan, Biden turned to his Senate vote in October 2002 to authorize Bush to use military force against Iraq.", "url": "https://www.cnn.com/2019/12/31/politics/fact-check-biden-buttigieg-iraq-afghanistan/index.html"}, {"question": "Did Joe Biden vote in favor of military intervention in Iraq under specific circumstances?", "answer": "He didn't publicly raise doubts about U.S. intelligence that Iraq possessed WMDs until 2003, and he voted in favor of military intervention under specific circumstances, which was defeated in favor of the broader authorization approved by Congress.", "url": "https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/2020-election/sanders-opposition-iraq-war-was-more-complicated-he-presents-n1137541"}], "pred_label": "Refuted", "llm_output": "<|start_header_id|>assistant<|end_header_id|>

