{"claim_id": 10, "claim": "Biden has pledged to defund the police", "evidence": [{"question": "Does Joe Biden's police reform plan involve defunding the police?", "answer": "In fact, Biden’s police reform plan calls for $300 million in funding for community-oriented policing, a portion of which would go toward hiring more police, which has been sharply criticized by some progressive Democrats.", "url": "https://abcnews.go.com/Politics/fact-check-biden-trump-rival-defund-police/story?id=72554629"}, {"question": "What specific reforms to policing did Biden's criminal justice plan propose?", "answer": "Biden unveiled a criminal justice plan last year that tackled reforms to policing. The proposal calls for an injection of $300 million into the Community Oriented Policing Services program, which authorized money for the hiring of more police officers and policing training.", "url": "https://www.cbsnews.com/news/joe-biden-not-in-favor-of-defunding-police-campaign-says/"}, {"question": "Does Joe Biden support the idea of defunding the police?", "answer": "Biden’s campaign rejected the phrase “defund the police” and called for more funding for police departments to implement policy changes.", "url": "https://www.cnn.com/2020/06/08/politics/joe-biden-defund-the-police/index.html"}, {"question": "Does Joe Biden support defunding the police, or does he support conditioning federal aid to police departments based on certain standards?", "answer": "Former Vice President Joe Biden says he doesn't support defunding police, but he does support conditioning federal aid on whether police meet "certain basic standards of decency and honorableness."", "url": "https://www.cbsnews.com/news/biden-federal-aid-police-epartments-defunding/"}, {"question": "Does Joe Biden support defunding the police?", "answer": "“I do not support defunding police,” Biden wrote in an op-ed for USA Today. “The better answer is to give police departments the resources they need to implement meaningful reforms, and to condition other federal dollars on completing those reforms.", "url": "https://theintercept.com/2020/06/11/defund-the-police-joe-biden-cops/"}, {"question": "Does Joe Biden support the slogan "defund the police"?", "answer": "Biden's opposition to defunding police departments puts him at odds with activists and some progressive lawmakers who have amplified the slogan "defund the police" during demonstrations that have erupted nationwide in the wake of George Floyd's death in Minneapolis.", "url": "https://www.cbsnews.com/news/joe-biden-not-in-favor-of-defunding-police-campaign-says/"}, {"question": "Does Joe Biden support defunding the police?", "answer": "Presumptive Democratic nominee Joe Biden definitively declared "I do not support defunding police," in an op-ed Wednesday, as protesters around the country increase their calls for overhauling the criminal justice system and President Trump attempts to tie Biden to the "Defund the police" movement.", "url": "https://www.forbes.com/sites/tommybeer/2020/06/10/joe-biden-declares-definitively-i-do-not-support-defunding-police/"}, {"question": "Does Joe Biden support reducing the budget for local police departments?", "answer": "Biden’s campaign had said earlier Monday that he backs advocates’ calls to increase spending on social programs separate from local police budgets, but he also wants more funding for police reforms such as body cameras and training on community policing approaches.", "url": "https://www.cnn.com/2020/06/08/politics/joe-biden-defund-the-police/index.html"}, {"question": "What did Joe Biden suggest doing with police funding in the context of the interview with Ady Barkan?", "answer": "In fact, Biden was responding to a question not about defunding the police but about shifting some funding to social service agencies: “But do we agree that we can redirect some of the funding?” progressive activist Ady Barkan asked in a July 8 interview.", "url": "https://www.factcheck.org/2020/07/trumps-false-recurring-claim-about-bidens-stance-on-police/"}, {"question": "Does the phrase "defund the police" refer to eliminating police departments entirely or revisiting their functions and shifting funding to other services?", "answer": "While some argue police departments should be eliminated entirely, as PolitiFact National detailed in a June 9, 2020 article, the use of the phrase "defund the police" more typically means to revisit the functions of police departments and shift funding toward, for instance, mental health and social services.", "url": "https://www.politifact.com/factchecks/2020/aug/05/donald-trump/no-joe-biden-isnt-board-defunding-police/"}], "pred_label": "Refuted", "llm_output": "<|start_header_id|>assistant<|end_header_id|>

justification: Biden has said he does not support defunding the police.

