ces, rather than tracking users' locations?", "answer": "Those concerns were why Apple and Google turned to Bluetooth to power its Exposure Notification System, which allows for phones to exchange beacons with other devices that have downloaded an app developed by a public health authority.", "url": "https://iapp.org/news/a/google-apple-outline-privacy-considerations-within-exposure-notification-system/"}, {"question": "Does the COVID-19 Exposure Notification System collect or use location data from users' devices?", "answer": "Our technology is designed to make these apps work better. Each user gets to decide whether or not to opt-in to Exposure Notifications; the system does not collect or use location from the device; and if a person is diagnosed with COVID-19, it is up to them whether or not to report that in the public health app.”", "url": "https://healthitanalytics.com/news/3-states-to-use-apple-google-covid-19-contact-tracing-system"}, {"question": "Does the COVID-19 Exposure Notification System share location information with other phones?", "answer": "When you turn on Exposure Notifications within an app from your region's government public health authority, your phone shares random IDs with other nearby phones that also have turned on the Exposure Notifications System.", "url": "https://en-emea.support.motorola.com/app/answers/detail/a_id/151888/p/11070"}, {"question": "Does the COVID-19 Exposure Notification System require users to opt-in before it can track their location?", "answer": "Apple and Google did recently add exposure notifications to devices under Settings, but the contact tracing technology works only if one has opted in and enabled the notifications.", "url": "https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/factcheck/2020/06/14/fact-check-android-users-must-opt-into-covid-19-tracing-technology/5341250002/"}, {"question": "Does the COVID-19 Exposure Notification System allow for the tracking of users' locations over time?", "answer": "The exposure notif