roposed to address the Affordable Care Act?", "answer": "The president can't repeal the health care law himself, but Trump and other Republicans have vowed to repeal and replace the Affordable Care Act, which is widely known as Obamacare.", "url": "https://www.nbcnews.com/storyline/inauguration-2017/trump-signs-executive-action-obamacare-inauguration-day-n710116"}, {"question": "What is Donald Trump's intention regarding the Affordable Care Act?", "answer": "One of President Trump's first official actions was to sign an executive order affirming the administration's intent to seek repeal of the Affordable Care Act (ACA) and directing federal agencies to minimize the economic and regulatory burdens of the ACA to the fullest extent permitted by law.", "url": "https://www.venable.com/insights/publications/2017/02/congress-continues-to-consider-its-affordable-care"}, {"question": "What is Donald Trump's intention regarding the Affordable Care Act?", "answer": "President Trump has made clear that his goal remains to repeal the Affordable Care Act (ACA), including its expansion of Medicaid to low-income adults, and to impose rigid caps on the federal government’s Medicaid spending.", "url": "https://www.cbpp.org/research/health/trump-administrations-harmful-changes-to-medicaid"}, {"question": "What impact have the Trump administration's repeal efforts had on the cost of health care coverage in the individual market?", "answer": "More than 18 months into the Trump presidency, the ACA remains largely in place. The cost of coverage in the individual market for people who lack subsidies has grown substantially, in large part because of the instability created by administration and congressional repeal efforts.", "url": "https://www.commonwealthfund.org/blog/2018/affordable-care-act-under-trump-administration"}, {"question": "Has Donald Trump consistently expressed opposition to the Affordable Care Act since his 2016 campaign?", "answer": "President Trump has endorsed repealin