ctive in curing migraines?", "answer": "Although studies are few and have found conflicting results, some people may find that acupuncture helps relieve symptoms of sinusitis.", "url": "https://www.mountsinai.org/health-library/condition/sinus-headache"}, {"question": "Is warm water effective in treating non-migraine headaches?", "answer": "And, according to National Headache Institute, using cold packs on your head works best for people who have a type of migraine with visual aura symptoms, while heat is more likely to work on other kinds of non-migraine headaches.", "url": "https://www.withcove.com/learn/migraine-home-remedies"}], "pred_label": "Refuted", "llm_output": "<|start_header_id|>assistant<|end_header_id|>

