mes built?", "answer": "Critics of Kiwibuild argue that the program won’t result in many extra homes being built. It’s a valid criticism.", "url": "https://www.greaterauckland.org.nz/2018/03/12/kiwibuild-good-vague-ugly-part-1/"}, {"question": "Does the Housing Minister think the original goal of delivering 100,000 KiwiBuild houses was realistic?", "answer": "In announcing the KiwiBuild reset on Wednesday, Housing Minister Megan Woods said the 100,000 homes goal was "overly ambitious".", "url": "https://www.newshub.co.nz/home/politics/2019/09/labour-s-flagship-policy-where-did-kiwibuild-go-wrong.html"}, {"question": "Is the target of 16,000 Kiwibuild homes by now a realistic expectation?", "answer": "The 10-year target is 100,000 Kiwibuild homes, but Shamubeel Eaqub says we need half a million, and with perhaps a bit of bravado, the Housing Minister replied that he expects to build “far more” than the targeted 100,000.", "url": "https://www.greaterauckland.org.nz/2018/03/12/kiwibuild-good-vague-ugly-part-1/"}, {"question": "Did the NZ Green Party deliver 16,000 KiwiBuild houses by 30 June 2020?", "answer": "Hon Judith Collins: When her Government promised to build 16,000 KiwiBuild homes in the first three years of the KiwiBuild programme, then delivered only 452 houses, as at 30 June 2020, was that a failure to deliver?", "url": "https://www.scoop.co.nz/stories/PA2008/S00024/parliament-oral-questions-questions-to-ministers.htm"}, {"question": "Does the claim that the NZ Green Party should have delivered 16,000 KiwiBuild houses by now (10/08/2020) accurately reflect the actual impact of the KiwiBuild program on the overall number of houses built in New Zealand?", "answer": "Compared with the numbers above, Kiwibuild has very significant scale. If we assume that all Kiwibuild homes wouldn’t otherwise have been built (this is very optimistic, of course) then the program would lift home building numbers by 40% across the country, or by 66% in Auckland.", "url": "https:/