nding won't drop. Money will be transferred from the federal government's general fund to the Social Security trust funds to cover any payroll tax amounts not collected, according to Mnuchin.", "url": "https://www.kiplinger.com/taxes/601197/what-trumps-payroll-tax-cut-will-mean-for-you"}, {"question": "What types of employees are eligible for Donald Trump's payroll tax deferral?", "answer": "The payroll tax deferral is set to begin for wages paid September 1. It only applies to employees who make less than $4,000 on a bi-weekly basis (or, if a different payment schedule is used, it generally applies to employees making less than $104,000 per year).", "url": "https://www.mcgrathnorth.com/publications/president-trumps-payroll-tax-deferral-what-we-do-and-dont-know"}, {"question": "What is the income threshold for workers who will be exempt from paying Social Security payroll taxes under Trump's executive order?", "answer": "One of the executive orders (actually an executive "memorandum") suspends the collection of Social Security payroll taxes from September 1 until the end of the year for workers making less than $4,000 for any bi-weekly pay period (that's $2,000 per week, or $104,000 per year).", "url": "https://www.kiplinger.com/taxes/601197/what-trumps-payroll-tax-cut-will-mean-for-you"}, {"question": "What is the income threshold for American workers to be eligible for Trump's payroll tax deferral?", "answer": "Under the president's executive order, your share of Social Security taxes (6.2%) won't be taken out of your paycheck if your pre-tax bi-weekly salary is $4,000 or less.", "url": "https://www.kiplinger.com/taxes/601197/what-trumps-payroll-tax-cut-will-mean-for-you"}, {"question": "How much could American workers potentially owe in back taxes after the Trump payroll tax deferral ends?", "answer": "Since the executive order doesn't apply to bi-weekly wages above $4,000, the maximum tax deferral is $124 per week, which would add up to $2,232 from September 1 to December 31.", "url": "https://www.kiplinger.com/taxes/601197/what-trumps-payroll-tax-cut-will-mean-for-you"}, {"question": "How would the payroll tax deferral affect American workers in terms of their tax liability during tax season?", "answer": "In essence, the deferral is an interest-free loan that would have to be repaid. Trump said he’ll try to get lawmakers to extend it, and the timing would line up with a post-election lame-duck session in which Congress will try to pass government funding bills.", "url": "https://news.wttw.com/2020/08/08/trump-orders-more-unemployment-pay-payroll-tax-deferral"}], "pred_label": "Supported", "llm_output": "<|start_header_id|>assistant<|end_header_id|>

