{"claim_id": 156, "claim": "You can test too much for Covid-19.", "evidence": [{"question": "Does the increase in COVID-19 cases reflect an improvement in testing capabilities rather than an actual rise in infections?", "answer": ""That states are finding more cases relative to the amount of tests they are conducting provides the strongest rebuttal to the administration's assertion that case numbers are rising because we're getting better at finding cases through increased testing," Jennifer Nuzzo, lead epidemiologist of Johns Hopkins University's Covid-19 Testing Insights Initiative, wrote in an op-ed for The Washington Post.", "url": "https://www.cnbc.com/2020/06/23/trump-blames-rise-in-coronavirus-cases-on-testing-despite-signs-of-spread.html"}, {"question": "What does the positivity rate indicate about the relationship between the number of COVID-19 tests and the number of positive cases?", "answer": "To dispel claims that testing is to blame for the country's growing outbreak, epidemiologists point to a figure known as the positivity rate, which indicates the percent of tests that come back positive in a given region.", "url": "https://www.cnbc.com/2020/06/23/trump-blames-rise-in-coronavirus-cases-on-testing-despite-signs-of-spread.html"}, {"question": "Is there a mismatch between the current level of COVID-19 testing and the rate of transmission?", "answer": "“This suggests that testing capacity is lagging behind levels of transmission. Indeed testing is not available for all who seek it in our state, and delays in test acquisition and receipt of results weaken the utility of those tests in preventing spread.”", "url": "https://www.factcheck.org/2020/06/trump-falsely-says-covid-19-surge-only-due-to-testing-misleads-on-deaths/"}, {"question": "What is the relationship between the increase in COVID-19 testing and the rise in positive test results?", "answer": "Increased testing does contribute to the higher numbers, but there’s more to it. Testing in fact has uncovered a worrisome trend: The percentage of tests coming back positive for the virus is on the rise across nearly the entire country.", "url": "https://apnews.com/article/travel-police-reform-latin-america-china-ap-fact-check-0aa783aa734b2ac3d984c5116b3e8039"}, {"question": "What is the basis for Trump's claim that increased testing is the cause of the surge in COVID-19 cases?", "answer": "Nevertheless, Trump continues to perpetuate the false idea that testing — and testing alone — is why the U.S. is seeing a surge in cases, despite mounting hospitalizations and a rise in the percentage of tests coming back positive in certain parts of the country.", "url": "https://www.factcheck.org/2020/06/trump-falsely-says-covid-19-surge-only-due-to-testing-misleads-on-deaths/"}, {"question": "What is the relationship between increased COVID-19 testing and the rising percentage of positive test results?", "answer": "Increased testing does play a role in the higher numbers, but there’s more to it. Testing in fact has uncovered a worrisome trend: The percentage of tests coming back positive for the virus is on the rise across nearly the entire country.", "url": "https://www.pbs.org/newshour/politics/ap-fact-check-trump-bending-facts-on-virus-biden-economy"}, {"question": "Why are people having trouble getting tested for COVID-19?", "answer": "Early missteps with test kits developed by the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention, coupled with strict government criteria about who qualified for screening, have led to widespread reports of people struggling to get tested.", "url": "https://www.cbsnews.com/boston/news/athletes-celebrities-get-coronavirus-tests-raising-concerns-of-inequality/"}, {"question": "What are the implications of making COVID-19 testing widely available?", "answer": "In order to contain this COVID-19 epidemic, affordable testing must be available to quickly identify patients with the virus and mitigate community spread.", "url": "https://schakowsky.house.gov/media/press-releases/too-much-stake-delay-or-profiteering-schakowsky-doggett-delauro-press"}, {"question": "What has been the result of the increased availability of COVID-19 testing in the last two weeks?", "answer": "Over the last two weeks, that has led to a surge in testing available from private doctors and labs not bound by CDC's criteria for which patients should be prioritized for testing, such as those with fever and difficulty breathing who have recently traveled to affected countries overseas, or those who have had close contact with someone confirmed to have had the virus.", "url": "https://www.cbsnews.com/boston/news/athletes-celebrities-get-coronavirus-tests-raising-concerns-of-inequality/"}, {"question": "What factors contributed to the delayed rollout of COVID-19 testing in the US?", "answer": "Experts agree that widespread early testing would have been key to containing the virus, but the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention and the FDA bungled the rollout of tests thanks to a bad early batch and enforcement of agency rules that restricted both who could be tested and the private sector’s ability to roll out new tests.", "url": "https://www.theatlantic.com/ideas/archive/2020/03/isnt-all-trumps-fault-he-isnt-helping-either/609052/"}], "pred_label": "Refuted", "llm_output": "<|start_header_id|>assistant<|end_header_id|>

