ar, said Martin Luther King Jr.", "url": "https://abcnews.go.com/Politics/rep-john-lewis-meeting-trump-martin-luther-king/story?id=52343117"}, {"question": "Did John Lewis refuse to attend Trump's inauguration and State of the Union speeches?", "answer": "Lewis refused to attend Trump’s inauguration or State of the Union addresses. In one of his final media appearances after being diagnosed with advanced pancreatic cancer, he walked a street near the White House painted with a Black Lives Matter mural.", "url": "https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/jul/18/john-lewis-from-civil-rights-titan-to-black-lives-matter"}, {"question": "Did John Lewis attend Trump's inauguration?", "answer": "On NBC’s “Meet the Press,” Rep. John Lewis said he will boycott President-elect Donald Trump’s inauguration, claiming it will be the first time he has missed a presidential inauguration since joining Congress 30 years ago.", "url": "https://www.factcheck.org/2017/01/lewis-skipped-bushs-inauguration-too/"}, {"question": "What was the reason for the boycott of Donald Trump's inauguration by some legislators after his attacks against Rep. John Lewis?", "answer": "After Donald Trump’s attacks against civil rights legend Rep. John Lewis, more legislators are rushing to boycott the president-elect’s upcoming inauguration, citing his feud with the Georgia Democrat as the last straw in their decision.", "url": "https://www.cbsnews.com/news/trumps-john-lewis-comments-drive-more-democrats-away-from-inauguration/"}, {"question": "Why did John Lewis refuse to attend Trump's inauguration?", "answer": "John Lewis refused to attend Trump’s inauguration. He said that that Russian interference in the campaign was unfair and the election “illegitimate.”", "url": "https://www.newyorker.com/news/daily-comment/the-ongoing-struggle-of-john-lewis"}, {"question": "Did Rep. John Lewis plan to attend Trump's State of the Union address after Trump made certain comments?", "answer": "In the wake of those remarks