{"claim_id": 160, "claim": "California is going to send tens of millions of ballots to California, all over the place.", "evidence": [{"question": "Has the number of people requesting mail-in ballots in California increased over time?", "answer": "California traditionally has offered mail-in voting only to those who request ballots. Over time the number has grown to represent more than half of all cast ballots.", "url": "https://www.pbs.org/newshour/nation/california-rejected-100000-mail-in-ballots-because-of-mistakes"}, {"question": "Are all the tens of millions of ballots being sent by California going to registered voters?", "answer": "Sam Mahood, press secretary for California’s secretary of state, reiterated that in an email to FactCheck.org, saying: “Vote-by-mail ballots will only be sent to active registered voters ahead of the November 3, 2020 General Election.”", "url": "https://www.factcheck.org/2020/05/more-false-mail-in-ballot-claims-from-trump/"}, {"question": "Is California sending mail-in ballots to all registered voters in the state for the November election?", "answer": "In response to the coronavirus outbreak, Democratic Gov. Gavin Newsom in June signed a law requiring county election officials to mail a ballot to all the state’s nearly 21 million registered voters for the November election.", "url": "https://www.pbs.org/newshour/nation/california-rejected-100000-mail-in-ballots-because-of-mistakes"}, {"question": "Are the tens of millions of ballots being sent by California going to registered voters?", "answer": "Newsom’s May 8 executive order pertained to registered voters. It said that due to the potential threat of COVID-19 in November “each county elections officials shall transmit vote-by-mail ballots for the November 3, 2020 General Election to all voters who are, as of the last day on which vote-by-mail ballots may be transmitted to voters in connection with that election, registered to vote in that election.”", "url": "https://www.factcheck.org/2020/05/more-false-mail-in-ballot-claims-from-trump/"}, {"question": "Are all registered voters in California set to receive a mail-in ballot due to the pandemic?", "answer": "The pandemic has driven lawmakers to act, such as California Gov. Gavin Newsom, who issued an order that requires election officials in each of the state's 58 counties to send mail-in ballots to all registered voters.", "url": "https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/donald-trump/twitter-fact-checks-trump-s-misleading-tweet-mail-voting-n1215151"}, {"question": "Is the claim that California is sending tens of millions of ballots to anyone living in the state accurate?", "answer": "In reality, Newsom ordered counties to send mail-in ballots only to registered voters in California, hardly to "anyone living in the state."", "url": "https://www.politifact.com/factchecks/2020/may/26/donald-trump/no-california-not-sending-mail-ballots-anyone-stat/"}, {"question": "Did Trump claim that California would send tens of millions of ballots to anyone living in the state?", "answer": "A review of Newsom’s executive order shows only registered voters would receive vote-by-mail ballots, not "anyone living in the state," as Trump claimed.", "url": "https://www.politifact.com/factchecks/2020/may/26/donald-trump/no-california-not-sending-mail-ballots-anyone-stat/"}, {"question": "Where will the tens of millions of ballots be mailed to in California?", "answer": "Secretary of State Alex Padilla said in a May 8 press release the ballots would be mailed to registered voters living domestically 29 days before the Nov. 3 Election Day.", "url": "https://www.factcheck.org/2020/05/more-false-mail-in-ballot-claims-from-trump/"}, {"question": "Are the tens of millions of ballots being sent by California going to registered voters?", "answer": "“Each county elections officials shall transmit vote-by-mail ballots for the November 3, 2020 General Election to all voters who are, as of the last day on which vote-by-mail ballots may be transmitted to voters in connection with that election, registered to vote in that election,” the order reads in part.", "url": "https://www.cnn.com/2020/05/26/politics/fact-check-trump-vote-by-mail-fraud-gavin-newsom-california/index.html"}, {"question": "In states that conduct all-mail elections, have there been widespread or coordinated instances of voter fraud?", "answer": "Colorado, Hawaii, Oregon, Utah and Washington already conduct all-mail elections where ballots are sent to registered voters, and while the states reported seeing isolated cases of fraud none have described widespread or coordinated instances at levels greater than most other non-all-mail voting states.", "url": "https://abcnews.go.com/Politics/election-officials-dozens-states-dispute-president-trumps-claim/story?id=71833120"}], "pred_label": "Refuted", "llm_output": "<|start_header_id|>assistant<|end_header_id|>

